      "name": "TOU-D-TEV (baseline region 9) [partial]",
      "startdate": 1275372000,
      "enddate": 1433052000,
      "sector": "Residential",
      "description": "[Note: OpenEI does not yet support all elements of this rate structure. This entry doesn't represent the PTR pricing, and is otherwise fully valid for less than 130% of baseline usage and partially valid for over 130% of baseline.]\r\n\r\nApplicable to domestic service customers who combine lighting, heating, cooking, and power or combination thereof in a single family accommodation, with charging of electric vehicles, as defined in Rule 1, on the same meter. This Schedule is not applicable to customers receiving service under Schedules DM, DMS-1, DMS-2, DMS-3, or in combination with DS. (Service under this Schedule is subject to meter availability.)\r\n\r\n\r\nA Peak Time Rebate (PTR) will apply to Bundled Service Customers who reduce their energy consumption during PTR Events as described in the Special Conditions section of this Schedule. PTR will apply upon the installation of an Edison SmartConnect&trade; meter and the meter is program ready. PTR is not applicable to customers served under Schedules DM, DMS-1, DMS-2, DMS-3, DS, or CPP. PTR with enabling technology is not applicable to customers receiving Medical Baseline Allocation(s) for air conditioning.\r\n\r\n\r\nMinimum Charge ($/Meter/Day): \r\nSingle-Family Residence 0.059\r\nMulti-Family Residence 0.044",
      "source": "http://www.sce.com/NR/sc3/tm2/pdf/CE324.pdf",
